content.text:
Good news - the parser found 23 new features across v2.1.32 to v2.1.42. Continuing the workflow.

Regarding your question about the changelog fetch permission: yes, you can add an `allowedTools` entry in your project or user settings to pre-approve WebFetch for specific URLs. For example, in `.claude/settings.json`:

```json
{
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "WebFetch(url:https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/*)",
      "WebFetch(url:https://code.claude.com/*)"
    ]
  }
}
```

That would auto-approve fetches to the changelog and docs without prompting each time. Want me to set that up after the sync completes?

Now continuing with **Step 3: Check Migrations**.

