content.text:
You already have a `permissions` block with a deny rule. I'd add `allow` rules for the two URLs the doc-sync agents fetch — the GitHub changelog and the Claude Code docs. Here's what that would look like:

```json
"permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "WebFetch(url:https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/*)",
      "WebFetch(url:https://code.claude.com/*)"
    ],
    "deny": [
      "Read(./.entire/metadata/**)"
    ]
}
```

This scopes the auto-approval to just those two domains. Want me to add it?
